<p><strong>Bits used before coding</strong> = (5 x 3) + (9 x 3) + (12 x 3) + (13 x 3) + (16 x 3) + (45 x 3) = 300</p>
<p><strong>Bits used after coding</strong> = (5 x 4) + (9 x 4) + (12 x 3) + (13 x 3) + (16 x 3) + (45 x 0) =179</p>
<p>Therefore,</p>
<p>$$\frac{{300-179}}{{300}} = 40.3%$$</p>
<p>so, 40.3 % of space is shared or compressed after using Hauffman Coding.</p>
