<h3>Question 6</h3>
<div><p><p>Explain the computer based animation.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p><strong>Computer based Animation</strong> is an animation performed by computer using graphical tools to produce visual effects. To animate something is like injecting life to it. Basic steps for computer basedanimation are:</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li><strong>Input Process</strong> : At the initial stage of generating animation, the drawing must be digitized in order to generate key frames. for digitizing the drawings the method of optical scanning, tracing along with data tablet is used.</li>
<li><strong>Composition stage</strong> : In this stage the foreground and background figures are combined to generate the individual frames for the final animation.</li>
<li><strong>In between process</strong> : the animation of movement from one position to another needs a composition of frames with intermediate frames in betweeen key frames. This is called in between process, which is created out by the interpolation method.</li>
<li><strong>Changing colors</strong> : For changing colors, computer aided animation uses LUt or CLUT (Color LookUp Table) in a frame buffer and process of double buffering. The LUT animation is generated by manipulating the color loopup table. This simplest method is to cycle the color in LUT.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<h3>Question 7</h3>
<div><p><p>How speech is generated? Describe.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>Speech generation is the computer &#8211; generated simulation of human speech. It contain following steps for generation of speech:</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li><strong>Basic notations</strong> : Speech consist of fundamental frequency as it&#8217;s component as it is used to present a voice of sound. A voiced sound is generated via vocal cords. It consist of morph, phoneme (allphone) as smallest speech unit. They can be represented in two ways and they are : Text notation and Phoneme notation. Text notations are usually the words and text which are converted to speech. Phoneme notation generate the speech depending on the concatenation of the phoneme sound and symbols sound.</li>
<li><strong>Reproduce speech output</strong> : The easy way to reproduce the speech output is to use the previously recorded speech and playing it back. Speech can be recorded as PCM (Pulse Code Modulation) or using the process of digitization of sound. It has two basic way to represent or produce the sound : Naturally produced sound and pre-recorded sound. Naturally produced sounds are the human sounds which are recorded as the input data are sometimes are used whiche generation of sound. Pre-recorded sounds are collected and concatenated based on the speech requirement and then the speech are generated.</li>
<li><strong>Time dependent sound concatenation</strong> : Speech generation/ output can also be performed by sound concatenation in a timely fashion. Individual speech units are composed like building blocks, where the composition can occur at different levels. In simplest case, the individual phones are understood as speech units. It is composed of some basic as timings and phoneme, syllables. Phoneme and Syllables are first collected from different sources and then they are concatenated over the time.</li>
<li><strong>Frequency dependent sound concatenation</strong> : Speech generation/ output can also be based on a frequency &#8211; dependent sound concatenation. Format are frequency maxima in the spectrum of the speech signal. Format synthesis simulates the vocal tract through a filter. It is composed of some basic as pitch, tones and voice influcation. Pitch and tones are focused and they are concatenated over the voice fluctuation based on the speech. The endings of sentences, breaking of the words high and low tones etc are maintained.</li>
</ul>
<p><img data-recalc-dims="1" loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-38947 aligncenter" src="https://i0.wp.com/hamrocsit.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/coomponent-of-speech-.drawio.png?resize=665%2C211&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="665" height="211"></p>
</div>
<h3>Question 8</h3>
<div><p><p>What are the multimedia interface component?</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>Multimedia interface component are the elements that allow user to interact with multimedia system. These components enable the integration of text, audio, video, graphics, and animation into a single interactive experience. Here are some key multimedia interface components:</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li><strong>Text</strong> : Text is the most basic component, used for displaying information, instructions, and interactive content. Text appears in all multimedia creations of some kind. Text in multimedia systems can communicate specific information or serve as a supplement to the information provided by the other media.</li>
<li><strong>Audio</strong> : Audio can be implemented at the user interface for application control. It includes sound effect, background music, narration and dilogue. Sound is the most serious aspect of multimedia, delivering the joy of music, special effects, and other forms of entertainment.</li>
<li><strong>Graphics</strong> : Graphics components include static images such as photographs, drawings, charts, and diagrams.  Graphics are at the heart of any multimedia presentation. Non-text information, such as a sketch, chart, or photograph, is represented digitally. Adobe Photoshop is a popular graphics editing program that allows you to effortlessly change graphics and make them more effective and appealing.</li>
<li><strong>Animation</strong> : Animation involves the use of moving graphics to create a dynamic and engaging experience. It’s a set of visuals that give the impression of movement. Animation is the process of making a still image appear to move. A presentation can also be made lighter and more appealing by using animation.</li>
<li><strong>Video</strong> : Video components involve the integration of moving images, which can include live-action footage, animations, or a combination of both. The term video refers to a moving image that is accompanied by sound, such as a television picture. Text can be included in videos, either as captioning for spoken words or as text embedded in an image, as in a slide presentation.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<h3>Question 9</h3>
<div><p><p>Discuss the animation language.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>Animation languages are specialized programming or scripting languages designed to create animations and control multimedia elements. Different languages for describing animation are:</p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Linear list Notations</span> : </strong></p>
<p>Linear list notation language is animation supporting language where each event in the animation is described by atarting and ending frame number and an action that has to take place. SCEFO (Scene Format) is example of linear list notation.</p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Graphical Language</span> : </strong></p>
<p>Graphical language describe animation in a more visual way than textual languages. This language is used for expressing and editing the changes in an animation. Auto CAD is an example of graphical language.</p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">General Purpose Language</span> : </strong></p>
<p>It is a high level language developed for normal application software development that support the features of animation along with graphic drawing. for example: C, C++, Java etc.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<h3>Question 10</h3>
<div><p><p>Explain the abstraction levels of programming.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p><img data-recalc-dims="1" loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="alignnone wp-image-38983 aligncenter" src="https://i0.wp.com/hamrocsit.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/abstraction-level.drawio.png?resize=393%2C467&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="393" height="467"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>fig: abstraction levels of programming of multimedia</strong></p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Abstraction level in programming defines different approaches with a varying degree of details for representing, accessing and manipulating data.</li>
<li>A device is not part of the operating system but is directly accessible to every component and application.</li>
<li>A library, the simplest abstraction level includes the necessary function for controlling the corresponding hardware with specific device access operation.</li>
<li>Device driver are simply the implementation of device access and scheduling.</li>
<li>Higher programming language contain abstraction of multimedia data.</li>
<li>An object oriented environment provides most flexibility for programmers.</li>
<li>A multimedia application may access each level.</li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<h3>Question 11</h3>
<div><p><p>Explain the application of multimedia in media integration.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>Media integration specifies relationships between various media elements to represent to represent and manipulate a multimedia object. It contains :</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Multimedia editor</li>
<li>Hypermedia/Hypertext editor</li>
<li>Authoring tools</li>
</ul>
<p>Application of multimedia in media integration can be as</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li><b>Virtual reality : </b>It is used to describe physical environments with the help of head-mounted displays. It is simulated experience in which user believe it as a real world. A person using VR equipment is able to look around the artificial world, more around in it.</li>
<li><strong>Interactive video</strong> : Interactive video research addresses various problems in the area of interactive TV and Video-on-Demand. Interactive TV specifies that the TV viewer can become more active participant than in the case today.</li>
<li><strong>Education and E-Learning </strong>: E-learning platforms integrate text, audio, video, animations, and interactive quizzes to enhance the learning experience. Multimedia tools like video conferencing, virtual whiteboards, and collaborative documents are used to facilitate online education.</li>
<li><strong>Healthcare </strong>: Multimedia tools like 3D animations, virtual reality (VR), and interactive simulations are used for medical education and training. Multimedia content, including instructional videos and interactive guides, helps patients understand medical procedures and treatment plans.</li>
<li><strong>E-Commerce </strong>: E-commerce platforms use multimedia, such as 360-degree product views, video demonstrations, and interactive features, to enhance product presentation. Augmented reality allows customers to virtually try on clothing, accessories, and makeup, providing an interactive shopping experience.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<h3>Question 12</h3>
<div><p><p>Explain the digital image representation with example.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><div class="flex-shrink-0 flex flex-col relative items-end">
<div>
<div class="pt-0">
<div class="gizmo-bot-avatar flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center overflow-hidden rounded-full">
<div class="relative p-1 rounded-sm flex items-center justify-center bg-token-main-surface-primary text-token-text-primary h-8 w-8">Digital image representation involves converting visual information into a format that a computer can store, process, and display. This process is typically done through the use of pixels and color models.</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Digital image is represented by matrix of numbeic values each representing a quantized intensity value. When I is two dimensional matrix, then I(r, c) is the intensity value at the position corresponding to row(r) and column(c) of the matrix.</li>
<li>The point at which an image is sampled are known as picture elements, commonly abbreviated as pixels.</li>
<li>If there are just two intensity values for example black and white, they are represented by the numbers 0 and 1; such images are called binary-valued images.</li>
<li>When 8 bit integers are used to store each pixel value, the gray levels range from 0 (black) to 255 (white).</li>
<li>An image composed of pixels in an electronics/ digital syatem is said to be digital image.</li>
<li>Digital image with higher dimension consist of higher no of pixels and vice versa which is directly proportional to quality of image.</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>For example</strong></span></p>
<p>Consider a simple 3&#215;3 RGB image. Each pixel&#8217;s color is represented by three values corresponding to red, green, and blue intensities. Here is an example of how such an image might be represented:</p>
